y":"GesmkMX2mM"},{"type":"text","value":" will take a raster input of a stream network and generate a new raster showing stream order. Stream order refers to a hierarchical network of streams, with higher order streams representing major waterways and first-order streams representing the smallest tributaries.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"nHkRii8JmZ"}],"key":"sgqjePz7Ez"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Input stream raster can be the flow accumulation raster, or a modified flow accumulation raster of streams above a defined threshold. Values below this threshold can be set to NoData using a SetNull operation in Raster Calculator:","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"DJGNy3kiFu"}],"key":"A8ZgDjE64o"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"SetNull(\"flow_accumulation.tif\" < 3500, \"flow_accumulation.tif\")","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"BjDyq8AmIB"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In this operation, the flow accumulation raster values below 3500 are set to NoData, otherwise values above 3500 keep the same values in the flow accumulation raster. The resulting raster surface shows streams classified based on stream order:","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"UoBBZuR72T"}],"key":"so8NuOM8vK"},{"type":"image","url":"/streamorder-39de24a45565a6eafadc60c667b28e98.jpg","alt":"Stream Order","width":"80%","align":"center","class":"bg-primary mb-1","key":"vk0Ffbeu80","urlSource":"/images/streamorder.jpg"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Basin","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"c